{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Eric García |image = |image size = |caption = |fullname = Eric García Martret |birth_date = {{birth date and age|2001|01|09|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/eric-garcia-martret/461179/|title=Eric García|website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=18 December 2018}}</ref> |birth_place = [[Barcelona]], Spain<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.footballdatabase.eu/en/player/details/324845-eric-garcia|title=Eric García|website=footballdatabase.eu |access-date=18 December 2018}}</ref> |height = {{height|meter=1.82}} |position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] |currentclub = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |clubnumber = 50 |youthclubs1 = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] |youthyears1 = 2008–2017 |youthclubs2 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |youthyears2 = 2017–2018 |clubs1 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |years1 = 2018– |caps1 = 0 |goals1 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2018–2019 |nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] |nationalcaps1 = 10 |nationalgoals1 = 2 |club-update = 29 January 2019 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 19:53, 18 December 2018 (UTC) }}
'''Eric García Martret''' (born 9 January 2001) is a Spanish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].
==Career== Born in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]], García was a youth product of ''[[Martorell]],'' the [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] academy. He joined Manchester City in the summer of 2017.<ref name="Goalcom">{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/ex-barcelona-jewel-eric-garcia-lighting-up-man-citys-pre/1lq7t2h0psoqc1h00gl47nvwk5|title=Ex-Barcelona jewel Eric Garcia lighting up Man City's pre-season|date=26 July 2018|work=Goal.com |accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref> García played with the first team as part of the 2018 summer pre-season.<ref name="Goalcom"/> On 18 December 2018, García made his first competitive start for Manchester City, playing in the [[EFL Cup]] match against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pollard |first1=Rob |title=De Bruyne and Aguero start, Garcia makes debut |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/december/leicester-man-city-team-news-tactics-injury-latest-carabao-cup |publisher=[[Manchester City F.C.]] |accessdate=18 December 2018}}</ref>
